The paper deals with streaming algorithms for graph problems, which are typically studied in the computer science subfield of data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of annotations to assist the streaming algorithm also involves communication complexity (cs.CC) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper also discusses results related to numerical linear algebra (cs.NA) in the streaming model.
